Super unique, super fun. Period. The puzzles were super interesting and engaging to figure out and gave such a rewarding feeling when you discover the solution. I heard about this game from Indie Game: The Movie and I fell in love with it from the second I saw it. I am so glad that I played it to its completion ([spoiler]209% :)[/spoiler]).

Ngl, this was the first and only video game to ever make me cry, for some reason. The emotions that were conveyed throughout it were unlike anything I've seen in a game. Call me soft or whatever, but it just goes to show how high of a tier this game sits on (at least for me).

I have thoroughly enjoyed my time playing this game, and I, being an aspiring indie game developer, look up to it a lot. Phil Fish may have left the games industry, but he hasn't left my mind. Him and his game give me motivation to keep working on projects and strive to be as successful and cool as this game is. I wish he would come back to keep developing games, but it doesn't look like that is gonna happen ;-;
